RESULTS
Labs:  White count 10.2.  Hemoglobin 8.1.  Platelets 251.  Creatinine 0.8.
I have also reviewed the preoperative imaging studies.
IMPRESSION/REPORT/PLAN
#1 Stage II (T2, N0, M0) adenocarcinoma of the appendix
We were able to share the preliminary pathology results with Mrs. Hildreth today.  We were able also to review their significance with her and her husband, most notably that we typically do not recommend adjuvant chemotherapy in the setting of stage II colon/appendiceal cancer.
We emphasized that we feel that her prognosis is quite good without any further treatment and that it would be reasonable for her to be followed in the GI Neoplasia Clinic for followup of this malignancy.  She should undergo a colonoscopy in one-year as part of this followup, and we emphasized this to her today.  This can be either scheduled at the time of her discharge to be coordinated with her other appointments (Cardiology, Endocrinology), or Mrs. Hildreth can contact her cardiologist Dr. Stewart to help coordinate this when she is due to come see him next.
Thank-you very much for involving us in Mrs. Hildreth's care.  We will not schedule her for any outpatient oncology followup; as mentioned above, she can follow-up with the GI Neoplasia Clinic.  Please feel free to contact us with questions or concerns via the medical oncology consult service pager (623-521-32968).
ADDENDUM:  Final pathology report as below consistent with preliminary results (marcus 9/8/10 0930)
A.  Colon, cecum, ascending, transverse, resection:  Invasive
moderately differentiated, grade 3 (of 4), adenocarcinoma, forming a
1.9 x 1.0 x 0.2 cm mass in the appendiceal orifice arising in a
background of appendiceal diffuse serrated adenoma.  Adenocarcinoma
invades into the muscularis propria.  The surgical resection margins
are negative for dysplasia and tumor.  Multiple (18) regional lymph
nodes are negative for tumor.  Biopsy site change is identified in
the ascending colon.  The bowel serosa is densely fibrotic,
predominantly in the ileum.
With available surgical material [AJCC pT2N0] (7th edition, 2010).

